The paper deals with the problem of storing dynamic data in distributed storage systems, which is a common topic in computer science. The use of erasure coding and key-value stores suggests that the paper may belong to the categories of Information Theory (cs.IT), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Social and Information Networks (cs.SI), or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI).
